<HEADLINE> Cambodian Prime Minister to Visit Singapore </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, May 30 (Xinhua) -- Prime Minister of the Kingdom of
Cambodia Hun Sen will pay an official visit to Singapore from June
1 to 3, 2000, at the invitation of his Singapore counterpart Goh
Chok Tong, Singapore Ministry of Foreign Affairs (MFA) announced
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
MFA said that Hun Sen will be accompanied by his wife, several
members of his Cabinet and other senior officials.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, Hun Sen and Goh Chok Tong will hold
discussions on bilateral relations, trade and investment issues
and other regional developments, MFA said.
</P>
<P>
Hun Sen will address the business community at a dinner hosted
by the Singapore Chinese Chamber of Commerce and Industry and
visit the Port of Singapore Authority as well as the Housing and
Development Board, MFA added.
</P>
<P>
Hun Sen's upcoming trip to Singapore will be the first official
visit to the city state by a Cambodian prime minister since the
armed conflicts that took place in the kingdom in 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
