<HEADLINE> South American Summit to Be Held in Brasilia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Velloso delivered to the Colombian Foreign Ministry the draft
of the communique to be issued by the South American summit, of
which the five big topics are democracy and human rights,
infrastructure, commerce, drugs and connected crimes, and
knowledge, information, and technology.
</P>
<P>
The regional event aims at "seeking to promote the integration
processes which the South American countries are negotiating among
themselves or with countries of other regions," said Velloso.
</P>
<P>
The summit is a project of President Cardoso, who taking
advantage of the symbolic celebration of Brazil discovery fifth
centennial, wanted to create a space to reflect "the South
American identity" and explore the possibilities for a regional
integration.  
</P>
</TEXT>
