<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brazil Supports Argentina's Economic Adjustment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Brazilian president said, commenting in Hanover, Germany,
the present economic situation of Argentina, that the situation in
that country is not easy and that Argentines are doing what they
must do.
</P>
<P>
"The Argentines have our solidarity, and I am confident that
Argentina will be able to retake the road of growing," said
Cardoso, who will inaugurate Wednesday in the German city the
Brazilian pavilion in the 2000 World Fair.
</P>
<P>
The Brazilian president said that the Argentine crisis will
have little impact on the Brazilian economy, remembering that
despite the 1998 Russian crisis, Brazil recorded a positive growth
and a small inflation last year.
</P>
<P>
"Brazil has already gone through all this and came out all
right We need not at all imitate what is occurring in Argentina,
because the situation is different," he said.
</P>
<P>
President Cardoso said that the differences between the
Brazilian and Argentine exchange regimes will not be an obstacle
for the strengthening of the Southern Common Market (Mercosur).
</P>
<P>
According to the Brazilian president, what is important for the
country of the economic block is to maintain their budget
stability and keep inflation under control.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
