<TEXT>
<P>
BOGOTA, May 31 (Xinhua) -- The Colombian National Army
confiscated 500 kilograms of cocaine and detained two adult men
and a minor during a crackdown in a neighborhood of Cali.
</P>
<P>
The army brigade deployed in the capital of the department said
Wednesday that the drug was ready for shipment abroad, probably
from the Buenaventura port, the first of Colombia on the Pacific
Ocean, west of Cali.
</P>
<P>
The drug traffickers were members of a ring known as "the
dolphins," said General Jaime Humberto Canal, who commands the
army brigade, with headquarters in Cali,
</P>
<P>
General Canal said that a special commando of his unit seized
the drug during a search and entry operation in a residence in the
south of Cali. 
