<HEADLINE> Turkey Ushers in Natural Disaster Task Force </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, May 31 (Xinhua) -- The Turkish Armed Forces (TSK) has
formed a task force to deal with natural disasters and provide
first-aid services, Anatolia News Agency reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Addressing an inauguration ceremony for the Natural Disasters
Search and Rescue Team, President Ahmet Necdet Sezer said it is not
possible to prevent natural disasters like earthquake and flood
from happening in Turkey, which suffers heavy human and property
losses due to frequent natural disasters.
</P>
<P>
However, "what is important is to be prepared against these
disasters and to take measures in time to minimize the disasters'
effects," he said.
</P>
<P>
Turkey has taken lessons from the two major earthquakes which
hit Turkey in August and November last year, said the president,
adding that "one of our biggest shortages in this field is the lack
of a well-trained, fully equipped, rescue team."
</P>
<P>
The Ankara-based team, equipped with the most advanced rescue
equipment, is capable of carrying out rescue operations in 18
different places, said the report.
</P>
<P>
Trained both at home and abroad, it is ready to provide first-
aid services around the clock and will also help train civil
defense organizations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
