<HEADLINE> Tanzanian President Urges Road Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Tanzanian President Benjamin
Mkapa has underlined the importance of good road network in his
government's efforts to fasten the development of the country.
</P>
<P>
Opening a meeting of road stakeholders here on Wednesday, the
president said infrastructure, especially roads, is a critical
factor for the success of the next phase reforms focused on faster
economic growth and fighting poverty.
</P>
<P>
A good road network of trunk, regional and rural roads is one
of the most important attributes to the development of any
society, Mkapa stressed.
</P>
<P>
"A well-developed and reliable road network will also increase
the level and quality of services provided to our people, and
expand economic opportunities available to them," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said good roads will enable farmers to get their inputs on
time and at lower cost, transport their produce to urban market
faster and will also help bring the inflation down.
</P>
<P>
In urban area, said Mkapa, good roads will encourage tourism
growth, create employment and facilitate the provision of social
services.
</P>
<P>
Tanzania's national road network is far from being established.
As a country with a land area of 886,040 square kilometers,
Tanzania has 88,200 kilometers of highways, among which more than
84,000 kilometers are unpaved roads. 
</P>
</TEXT>
