<HEADLINE> Qatar Urges Israel to Return All Lebanese Lands </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Qatar on Wednesday urged Israel
to fully withdraw from all Lebanese territories, including the
disputed Shebaa Farms.
</P>
<P>
The Qatari cabinet at a session called on Israel to
unconditionally implement U.N. Security Council Resolution 425
adopted in 1978 after Israel's first invasion, which calls for an
immediate and unconditional Israeli withdrawal from Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
Israel pulled out its troops from south Lebanon a week ago,
ending 22 years of occupation. But it refused to withdraw from the
Shebaa Farms, saying that the area belongs to Syria, not Lebanon.
</P>
