<HEADLINE> Iran Rejects Allegations of Arms Transfer to Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Foreign Ministry spokesman
Hamid Reza Asefi on Wednesday categorically rejected Israeli
allegations regarding arms shipment from Iran to Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
He said the great victory of the Lebanese resistance should be a
lesson for the Israeli government, the Islamic Republic News Agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
Following the victory of the Lebanese people in defeating the
Israeli force, Iran and other Muslim countries are ready to assist
Lebanon with its reconstruction, he added.
</P>
<P>
Israeli Foreign Minister David Levy said Tuesday Iran is
continuing to send arms to the Iran-backed Hezbollah guerrillas
which led the Lebanese resistance against the 22-year Israeli
occupation of southern Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
In an unexpected move, Israeli troops completed their withdrawal
from south Lebanon last week, which Iran termed as a victory for
the Islamic resistance in Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
Iran has refused to recognize Israel since the 1979 Islamic
revolution and openly supported armed struggle against Israeli
occupation of Islamic and Arab lands. 
</P>
