<HEADLINE> 7th E. Coli Death Confirmed, 2 More Being Probed in Canada </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, May 31 (Xinhua) -- The killer E. coli disease has
raised the death toll to seven in Canada's southern Ontario town
of Walkerton, with two additional reported deaths being
investigated, the local London Health Sciences Censer said
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The latest victims included an elderly and an unidentified
adult.
</P>
<P>
Another elderly patient at the Walkerton hospital is in a
critical condition with only palliative care while three of the 10
children remain in danger of life at the London Health Sciences
Center.
</P>
<P>
Up to 1,000 people in the small town of nearly 5,000 have been
stricken with diarrhea, nausea, headaches and fever in the worst
outbreak of E. coli 0-157.
</P>
<P>
Although health officials say the outbreak has passed its peak,
they expect it to take four weeks to have a conclusion of the
death toll.
</P>
<P>
The town's water supply is reported to be contaminated after a
rainstorm flooded the area. Angry locals are saying that they were
informed of the contamination too late. They accused local
utilities officials of failing to report the problem as soon as it
was first found. 
</P>
</TEXT>
