<HEADLINE> Bulgaria Convicts Turkish Man for Drug Trafficking </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, May 31 (Xinhua) -- A Bulgarian court Wednesday sentenced
a Turkish national to eight years in prison plus a fine for
smuggling 51 kilograms of heroin into the country, local media
reported.
</P>
<P>
Ismet Akasu, a 49-year-old Istanbul resident, was found guilty
by the District Court of Rousse. It was established that Akasu
smuggled the drugs into Bulgaria via the Kapitan Andreevo
Checkpoint on the Turkish border and transported them across the
country in an attempt to smuggle them out via the Danube Bridge
Checkpoint near Rousse.
</P>
<P>
The shipment, which consisted of 59 packs of heroin, was found
in December 1999 inside a spare tire of Akasu's truck, which was
intercepted in Rousse. 
</P>
