<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Syrian FM, U.N. Envoy Hold Talks in Damascus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Syrian Foreign Minister Faruk
Shareh held talks here Wednesday with visiting U.N. special envoy
to the Middle East Terje Roed-Larsen.
</P>
<P>
The talks focused on the details of the Israeli troop withdrawal
from south Lebanon last Wednesday and those related to the
controversial Shebaa Farms within the implementation of U.N.
Security Council resolution 425 of 1978, according to sources close
to Larsen.
</P>
<P>
Both Lebanon and Syria claimed that the fertile Shebaa Farms,
located at the western foothills of the Mount Hermon now under
Israeli occupation, belong to Lebanon and Israel should withdraw
its troops from the area.
</P>
<P>
However, Israel said the area is part of the Golan Heights it
captured from Syria in the 1967 Middle East war, whose fate should
be
decided during the peace talks with Syria after they resume.
</P>
<P>
The two also discussed the guarantees demanded by the U.N. for
international peacekeepers to be deployed in south Lebanon in the
wake of the withdrawal, the sources added.
</P>
<P>
Larsen arrived here from south Lebanon Wednesday morning for a
brief visit to Syria, the major power broker in Lebanon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
