<DOCNO> XIE20000531.0070 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Southwest China City Attracts Talent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Kunming city in southwest China's
Yunnan Province said that it will offer residential permits,
employment opportunities, government subsidies and housing for
talented people.
</P>
<P>
Acting Mayor Zhang Zhenguo said that the city will do all it
can to lure talent from all over the world in developing China's
relatively backward western areas.
</P>
<P>
The city will give a monthly subsidy of 5,000 yuan to a
scientist who bases his or her research in the city. It will also
award 10,000-300,000 yuan to researchers who have won national
prizes for their scientific research.
</P>
<P>
Kunming has already built two apartment buildings to house
talented Chinese from overseas.
</P>
</TEXT>
