<HEADLINE> Turkey Competes with Mexico to Host 2003 University Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, May 31 (Xinhua) -- The International University Sports
Federation (FISU) asked Turkey whether or not it is also willing
to host the games in 2005 prior to the voting which will be held
in Beijing, China, in July, according to the Anatolia News Agency
on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Kemal Tamer, Chairman of the Sports Federation, said that the
place of 2005 games will be determined in the meeting which will
be held in Beijing and asked Turkey's Youth and Sports General
Directorate what its opinion is.
</P>
<P>
Kemal Mutlu, Youth and Sports General Director, met with Ahmet
Pristina, Mayor of Izmir, and requested him to get prepared not
only for the 2003 games but also 2005 games.
</P>
<P>
Izmir, Turkey's third largest city on the coast of Aegean Sea,
would be the sponsor of the 2003 games.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, sources said that FISU chairman and general
secretary will visit Izmir between June 17 and 18 and hold
contacts regarding the 2003 sports.
</P>
<P>
Tamer said that the FISU deputy chairman is a Mexican and that
the Latin delegates are lobbying in favour of Mexico while the
European delegates are in favour of Turkey.
</P>
<P>
Tamer stated that they think that the International Federation
will decide to hold the 2005 games in Turkey but he is not sure
about where the 2003 games will be held.
</P>
<P>
Tamer added that he and general secretary Nihat Toker will join
the World University Sports Forum which will be held in Mexico
between June 28 and July 1. 
</P>
</TEXT>
