<HEADLINE> China's Aircraft Producer Delivers 1,000th Emergency Exit Hatches to Airbus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, May 31 (Xinhua) -- The Shenyang Aircraft Corporation
(SAC) Tuesday sent the 1000th emergency exit hatch to Airbus
Corporation.
</P>
<P>
SAC signed a contract with Airbus to produce emergency exit
hatches in 1986, the first subcontract China's aviation industry
signed with the European aviation industrial giant.
</P>
<P>
Li Fangyong, president of the SAC, said that all the 1,000
emergency exit hatches are of a high-quality.
</P>
<P>
Airbus would not only continue the subcontract, but let SAC
participate in making the wings for A320 planes, added Li.
</P>
<P>
Airbus currently has four Chinese partners producing airplane
parts, including Xi'an Aircraft Corporation, Shenyang Aircraft
Corporation, Guizhou Aviation Industrial Corporation and Chengdu
Aircraft Corporation.  
</P>
