<HEADLINE> More Favorable Policies to Woo Foreign Investment in Mineral Exploration: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 31 (Xinhua) -- China will formulate and issue more
preferential policies to encourage foreign investment in mineral
exploration, a Chinese official said here today.
</P>
<P>
Zhong Weizhi, Director of Geological Exploration Department
with the Ministry of Land and Resources, said six ministries with
the central government have reached a consensus on the policy.
</P>
<P>
The director said his ministry is still formulating
preferential regulations for those investing in western China or
remote and poor inland border areas.
</P>
<P>
Mining industries in western China have become a pillar
industry in the vast region, abundant in mineral resources,
accounting for 18 percent of the regional gross domestic product.
</P>
<P>
China has recently issued a number of preferential policies to
encourage foreign investment in mineral exploration in China.
</P>
<P>
Previously, foreign investors had to seek Chinese partners with
survey qualifications and mining rights to set up a joint venture
to obtain the rights of exploration in China and to conduct
geological surveys.
</P>
<P>
Western China is rich in mineral resources, including oil,
natural gas and coal. 
</P>
</TEXT>
