<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Syria Underlines European Role in Mideast Peace </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Assistant Secretary General of
Syrian ruling Baath Party Abdullah Al-Ahmar on Wednesday stressed
the importance of the European role in seriously seeking revival of
the peace process on the stalemated Syrian-Israeli track.
</P>
<P>
Ahmar made the remarks during his talks with a delegation from
the Socialist Group of the European Union.
</P>
<P>
He briefed the guests on the current situation in south Lebanon
after the latest Israeli pullout as well as the peace process on
the Syrian track which has been frozen since January 10.
</P>
<P>
The European side has to play a role in driving Israel towards
compliance with the basics of the process via fulfilment of the
obligations concerning full withdrawal from the occupied Arab
territories, He said.
</P>
<P>
On his part, the head of the EU delegation emphasized the
union's interest in the peace process and wished it success in
accordance with the international resolutions. He voiced hope that
the Euro-Mediterranean partnership would be fostered.
</P>
<P>
The two sides also took up the relations between the Syrian
ruling party and the Socialist parties in the European Union.
</P>
<P>
The European parliamentary delegation arrived in Damascus on
Monday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
