<HEADLINE> All Missing Persons on Sunken Boat Found </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Three people missing from a
tugboat which sank on the Pearl River on May 25 were found when
the boat was salvaged from the water and dragged to a local
shipyard today.
</P>
<P>
The Hangfeng No. 419 tugboat crashed into a 4,000-ton container
ship at 14:00 hours May 25 at the estuary of the Pearl River. Soon
after it rammed into the container ship, Xiangxu, all 14
passengers on the tugboat were thrown overboard. Eleven were
rescued from the river by passing ships.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the accident is still under investigation, said an
official of the Guangzhou Marine Salvation Bureau. 
</P>
