<HEADLINE> China Names Listed Company After Scientist </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Yuan Longping Agricultural High-
tech Co. Ltd issued 105 million shares, with one share valued at
12.98 yuan (1.56 U.S. dollars) at the Shenzhen Stock Exchange
today.
</P>
<P>
This is China's first listed company that is named after a
scientist.
</P>
<P>
The renowned Chinese scientist Yuan Longping, "father of China'
s hybrid rice" and the honorary chairman of the company, first
cultivated the hybrid rice in 1973. By the end of last year,
hybrid rice cultivated by Yuan had been planted in an area of 233
million hectares in China and has been introduced to dozens of
countries worldwide.
</P>
<P>
The Yuan Longping company is mainly engaged in research and
industrialization of agricultural high-tech products, with major
efforts extended in the cultivation of hybrid rice, hybrid pepper,
and various melons. The company also conducts breeding and
marketing of such high-tech crop seeds and saplings.
</P>
<P>
Experts pointed out that the listed company is good for Yuan in
publicizing and improving his hybrid rice.
</P>
<P>
The company has paid 5.8 million yuan to Yuan for use of his
name and as one of the people who founded the company, Yuan got 2.
5 million founder's shares by 3.79 million yuan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
