<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks Close Up 5.17 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks sharply grew 722.
96 points, or 5.17 percent, to close at 14,713.86 Wednesday,
breaking its 250-day moving average at 14,700.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said the market was boosted as a record gain in the
Nasdaq on Tuesday, and a telecom merger in Europe sent investors
flocking back to tech stocks.
</P>
<P>
China Telecom and Hutchison Whampoa, the telecom heavyweights,
led the charge as investor enthusiasm for local stocks
overshadowed the debut trading in Hong Kong of seven Nasdaq-listed
U.S. stocks.
</P>
<P>
Turnover totaled 17.963 billion HK dollars (2.303 billion U.S.
dollars), compared with Tuesday's 8.013 billion HK dollars (1.027
billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Of the four sub-indices of Hang Seng Index, Finance, Utilities,
Properties and Commerce and Industry went up 1.52 percent, 0.64
percent, 2.04 percent and 8.42 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng China Enterprises Index and the Hang Seng China-
Affiliated Corp Index gained 2.28 percent and 4.29 percent
respectively.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng IT Index rose 8.93 percent and the Hang Seng IT
Portfolio Index 6.70 percent.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong stocks soared 447.49 points, or 3.20 percent, to open
at 14,438.39 Wednesday and closed the morning session at 14,646.71.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
