<HEADLINE> Symposium on Advances in Social Welfare Held in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 31 (Xinhua) -- A symposium on advances in social
welfare in Hong Kong in the new millennium was held on May 30-31
by the Department of Social Work of the Chinese University of Hong
Kong.
</P>
<P>
The symposium is divided into two parts -- the advances on
social welfare services and social welfare research in Hong Kong.
Over 20 academics, experts and social workers were invited to
speak on various topics, including teenagers and elderly services,
poverty eradication and social security and youth work practices.
</P>
<P>
Speakers said the youth service institutions must take relevant
measures in response to the policy reform of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region government on social welfare and education.
</P>
<P>
As the information technology brings increasing impact to
people's lifestyle, it will be a major challenge for social
workers to improve their service to adapt to the new era, they
noted. 
