<HEADLINE> China to Host Nanyue Mountain Longevity Culture Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 31 (Xinhua) -- The 2000' China Nanyue Mountain
Longevity Culture Festival and Temple Fair to showcase traditional
culture and the new look of the Nanyue Mountain in central China
will be held on October 6-10 this year.
</P>
<P>
The event includes the performance of the tightrope walking
across two major peaks of the Nanyue Mountain, also known as Mt
Hengshan, the massive hot-air balloon flying, the large-scale
traditional temple fair and the trade show, said the sponsor, the
Party Committee and the People's Government of Hengyang City of
Hunan Province, Wednesday in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The highlight of the event will be the inauguration ceremony of
a giant quadripod, according to the sponsor. The quadripod, which
is 9.9 meters high and weighs 56 tons, is inscribed with 10,000
Chinese characters of different styles with the meaning of
longevity that symbolizes long-term prosperity of China.
</P>
<P>
Located around Hengyang City, Mt Hengshan is one of the five
famous mountains in China. As one of China's best known scenic
spots, Mt Hengshan receives more than 2 million visitors from at
home and abroad each year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
