<DOCNO> XIE20000531.0134 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Malaysia Lauds Europe's Role in Asia's Revival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia Wednesday lauded
Europe's role in Asia's economic revival, primarily by keeping
their economies open.
</P>
<P>
"Europe's facilitating role in Asia's recovery underscores the
linkages and level of interdependence between the economies of the
two regions," Malaysia's Deputy Prime Minister Abdullah Ahmad
Badawi said at the closing of a two-day Europe-Asia Business
Summit here.
</P>
<P>
He said Europe and Asia stand together now to further develop a
relationship built on mutual respect, and are creating a strategic
alliance among equals.
</P>
<P>
Although Asia-Europe cooperation in trade and investment has
remained strong since the colonial days, a more comprehensive
relationship was articulated in 1996 during the Asia-Europe summit
meeting held in Bangkok which began the ASEM process, he said.
</P>
<P>
"Subsequent ASEM meetings have strengthened the renewed efforts
at bridging the two continents, especially between two of the
world's most successful regional groupings -- the European Union
and ASEAN," he said.
</P>
<P>
Abdullah expressed his belief that the ASEM process will be an
important foundation for the development and strengthening of
future Asia-Europe cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He also believed that Europe and Asia have an important role to
play in reassessing the ugly side of globalization and
proliferation of information technology to ensure that ultimately
both remain in charge of the changes taking place.
</P>
<P>
Europe and Asia must forge a common platform on which to
articulate their concerns, he said, adding Asia-Europe relations
must address these concerns and focus on the challenges faced by
both regions.
</P>
<P>
At the business summit themed "Reshaping European-Southeast
Asian Business Ties: New Conditions, Shapes, Trends and
Opportunities," issues that were discussed included business
opportunities in Asia, development in transportation and
infrastructure, regional ports and airports, business
opportunities in Thailand after the economic crisis, business
opportunities in Europe, the multimedia super corridor in Malaysia
and the tourism industry.
</P>
<P>
The speakers included government ministers, corporate leaders
and business figures from Europe and Asia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
