<HEADLINE> Share Prices Close Mixed on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Share prices closed slightly
lower on the Singapore Stock Market Wednesday after a short-lived
surge in the morning session propelled by high-tech counters.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) ended 4.10 points lower
to close at 1,795.13 points, far off an all-day high of 1,852.63
points.
</P>
<P>
The total volume increased to 342.08 million shares valued at 1,
083.90 million Singapore dollars (630.17 million U.S. dollars).
Gainers outpaced losers by 173 to 125 with 245 counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Chartered continued to lead the actives chart with a turnover
of 21.48 million shares. It was followed by NatStl which had 14.58
million units done. Omni Ind was the next with 14.13 million
counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
Chartered also topped the gainers list as it shot up 240 cents
to close at 16.50 Singapore dollars. Venture gained 120 cents to
finish at 15.40 Singapore dollars. PacCent edged up 70 cents to
end at 12.00 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Asean was the biggest loser of the day sinking 160 cents to
close at 7.40 Singapore dollars. SCS lost 86 cents to finish at 3.
00 Singapore dollars. DBS shed 70 cents to end at 17.30 Singapore
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said the market was first encouraged by a record Nasdaq
surge as investors rushed in to buy in key high-tech shares.
</P>
<P>
U.S. stocks surged on Tuesday, driving the Nasdaq to its
highest-ever one-day percentage gain. The tech-heavy Nasdaq soared
7.94 percent or 254.37 to 3,459.48 points, just short of its
highest ever one-day points rise recorded six weeks ago.
</P>
<P>
However, analysts warned that the spate of bargain-hunting in
semiconductor and software shares that drove the Nasdaq up might
not signal an end to recent U.S. market volatility. 
</P>
</TEXT>
