<DOCNO> XIE20000531.0141 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ITU's Distance-Learning Course Attracts Latin Americans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, May 31 (Xinhua) -- A distance-learning course on
Telecommunication Regulation for Latin America has attracted a
record number of participants, the International Telecommunication
Union (ITU) said here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The popular distance-learning course, organized by the ITU
Telecommunication Development Bureau (BDT) under the "Centers of
Excellence" project, is being delivered over the Internet to
regulatory officials in Latin America through the ITU Virtual
Training Center (VTC).
</P>
<P>
The 10-week course was launched on April 3 and runs through
June 2, 2000.
</P>
<P>
Interest in the BDT regulatory distance-learning course has
surpassed all expectations, according to the ITU.
</P>
<P>
Over 120 regulatory officials throughout the Americas region
requested to participate in the course -- more than four times the
usual capacity of the VTC (30 participants).
</P>
<P>
Even though VTC capacity was increased to accept up to 50
participants, many prospective participants were placed on a
waiting list.
</P>
<P>
The BDT plans to re-offer the Latin American regulation course
during the second half of this year.
</P>
<P>
"E-learning is opening new horizons in the development of human
resources," said Hamadoun Toure, director of the ITU
Telecommunication Development Bureau.
</P>
<P>
"We expect that the experience gained in the course for the
Americas region will set the standard for all regions of the world,
" he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
