<HEADLINE> One Russian Serviceman Killed, 14 Injured in Blast EDS-Updates with new toll </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, May 31 (Xinhua) -- One Russian serviceman was killed
and 14 other injured in an explosion early Wednesday in Volgograd,
about 900 kilometers southwest of Moscow.
</P>
<P>
Four of the injured are listed in grave condition, the Interfax
news agency reported, quoting the Russian Emergency Situations
Ministry's press service.
</P>
<P>
An earlier report said that three Russian servicemen were
killed and eight wounded in the explosion.
</P>
<P>
The blast happened at 7.05 a.m. local time (0305 GMT) on the
city's Marshal Zhukov Avenue. A military garrison is located near
the scene of the blast.
</P>
<P>
The explosive device, reportedly tied to a tree, was set off at
the moment when a military unit was passing nearby in formation.
</P>
<P>
The independent NTV television reported that the explosion was
caused by a remote-controlled landmine stuffed with metal balls.
</P>
