<HEADLINE> Foreign Trade in Chongqing Increasing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Both the imports and exports of
Chongqing, the largest metropolis in southwestern China,
registered large increases in the first four months this year,
according to a foreign trade report released here today.
</P>
<P>
The city's imports increased by 70 percent to reach 270 million
U.S. dollars in the first four months, while exports doubled the
figure of last year's same period to reach 240 million U.S.
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Imports were characterized by general trade, with imports of
motor vehicles and motorcycles from Japan accounting for 70
percent of the total volume.
</P>
<P>
State-owned enterprises were the principle exporters, and it is
worth noting that the exports of private enterprises have
increased from two to 10 percent so far this year, with most of
their products going to Japan, Vietnam, the United States,
Indonesia, the Republic of Korea, and Hong Kong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
