<HEADLINE> Shandong Opens Tourism Website </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Internet surfers who are interested
in tourism information on east China's Shandong Province can now
access a new website, www.sdt.a.gov.cn, which officially opened
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
It is the largest Chinese website on the tourism industry,
according to Li Deming, director of the Shandong provincial
tourism bureau.
</P>
<P>
Before visiting the province for the first time, people can
browse the four million words of information in Chinese, English,
Japanese and Korean in more than 8,000 webpages. The coverage
involves tour sites, travel routes, weather, shopping, hotels,
recreational programs, customs and traditions in 51 cities and 48
tour destinations across the province.
</P>
<P>
The website also contains various columns on travel agencies,
currency exchange rate, complaint telephone numbers, and tour
guide consultations, the official said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
