<HEADLINE> CSSCI CD-ROM Makes Debut </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 31 (Xinhua) -- The CD-ROM of Chinese Social
Science Citation Index (CSSCI) made its debut here today, a
reflection of the development of China's social science research.
</P>
<P>
CSSCI, issued by Nanjing University in east China's Jiangsu
Province, was a key project of the Ministry of Education for 1999.
</P>
<P>
As a reference tool, CSSCI provides information on source
documents related to social sciences.
</P>
<P>
The CD-ROM gives an overall view of China's social scientific
research organizations, universities, and rankings according to
publication of Chinese social science articles.
</P>
<P>
An official from the Ministry of Education said that the
publication of CSSCI is sure to push forward Chinese social
science research as well as enhance the quality of social science
periodicals. 
</P>
