<HEADLINE> Share Prices Close Higher in Tokyo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Stock prices closed moderately higher
in Tokyo Wednesday, boosted by an overnight gain on Wall Street.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues on the First
Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange rose 103.55 points, or 0.64
percent, from Tuesday's close to end at 16,332.45.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), covering all
First Section issues, gained 4.41 points, or 0.29 percent, to 1,
522.84.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei hit the day's high of 16,538.67 shortly after
opening, topping 16,500 on an intraday basis for the first time in
seven trading days, after New York's technology-heavy NASDAQ
composite index posted a record percentage gain Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
But profit-taking or loss-cutting selling after recent gains
was stirred at that level, leading the key market gauge down to 16,
224.06 in the afternoon before it recovered moderately.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the major section increased to 609.52 million
shares from Tuesday's 489.17 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Toyobo, a leading spinning firm, was the day's volume leader.
</P>
<P>
Gainers included brokerage houses, nonferrous metal makers and
marine transportation firms.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, rubber, real estate and air transportation issues
saw large declines.
</P>
<P>
Of the issues listed on the First Section, gainers outnumbered
losers 715 to 526, with 154 issues closing unchanged. 
</P>
</TEXT>
