<HEADLINE> Israel Exhibits Hebrew Script Art in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 31 (Xinhua) -- An exhibition of Hebrew script art
sponsored by the Israeli Embassy in Beijing opened here today at
the Beijing University Library.
</P>
<P>
Items on display in the six-day show are either associated with
religious customs or used as ceremonial objects in Jewish homes or
synagogues.
</P>
<P>
The inscriptions on the items, in addition to their decorative
and artistic value, also serve as historical documentation. The
Hebrew letters, written by both trained scribes and folk artists,
show typical features of Jewish people living in different regions
of the world.
</P>
<P>
Ilan Mor, counselor of Israel to China, said at the opening
ceremony that the show will help further the mutual understanding
between Israeli and Chinese people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
