<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Urban Children Prefer To Be Teachers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Teaching is the future profession
most preferred by Chinese urban children, according to a recent
survey published in today's Beijing Daily.
</P>
<P>
The survey, which was carried out among children between the
ages of 6 and 15 in nine major cities, shows that nearly one out
of five urban children want to be teachers when they become adults.
</P>
<P>
The jobs of worker and farmer were the least favored by the
children surveyed, with only 0.8 and 0.3 percent of the total,
respectively, saying they might like these occupations. Some 16.9
percent of the children said they would like to be scientists, 15.
1 percent doctors, and three percent civil servants and 2.8
percent leading officials.
</P>
<P>
The survey also revealed that the older the children are, the
more likely they will choose well-paid professions, such as
entrepreneur, lawyer, or business people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
