<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Project Helps Girl Dropouts Return to School </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 31 (Xinhua) -- The Spring Bud Project, which is
initiated by the Children's Foundation of China, has helped more
than 900,000 girl dropouts return to school.
</P>
<P>
The project, which was started in 1989, has collected more than
300 million yuan (36 million US dollars) in donations.
</P>
<P>
The project has helped promote the education in poor rural
areas, said Gu Xiulian, vice-chairwoman of the foundation. She
added that the project will try to provide training of operative
technology to rural girls in the next phase.
</P>
<P>
She said that there are still large numbers of girl dropouts
among the poverty-stricken population, which accounted for 15
percent of the country's total poverty-stricken population.
</P>
<P>
She urged people from all walks of life to give more support to
the Spring Bud Project, and help more children return to school.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
