TOKYO -- Four Japanese opposition parties Wednesday submitted a
no-confidence motion against Prime Minister Yoshiro Mori's cabinet,
charging that Mori's controversial remark that Japan is a divine
nation centering on the emperor violated the country's
constitution.
</P>
<P>
The Democratic Party of Japan (DPJ), the Japanese Communist
Party (JCP), the Liberal Party (LP) and the Social Democratic
Party (SDP) filed the motion to the House of Representatives
shortly after a nonbinding censure resolution against Mori was
rejected in the House of Councilors. (Japan-Opposition-No
Confidence) 
</P>
