<HEADLINE> China News Digest: West on the Move (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 31 (Xinhua) -- China has adopted a strategy of
developing its vast western part, making it a key task in the
national economy this year and in coming years. Following are
major events on the western development this week:
</P>
<P>
Forum on Development of West China Held in Chengdu
</P>
<P>
Foreign businesspeople will get new opportunities as they are
encouraged to invest in China's vast western areas, said Liu
Zuozhang, deputy director of the Department of Foreign Investment
under MOFTEC, at a special forum on developing China's western
region in Chengdu, capital of southwest China's Sichuan Province.
He said that China has issued a number of new policies to lure
foreign investment since last year. Foreign investment is badly
needed in developing technological development in China's western
areas.
</P>
<P>
German Chain-Store Giant Opens Shop in Chongqing-- German
Metro, a transnational chain-store dealer, will invest 15 million
U.S. dollars in building the largest supermarket in the western
part of China. The supermarket will occupy two hectares of land in
downtown Chongqing on the southern bank of the Yangtze River.
</P>
<P>
Official Warns Against Redundant Construction Projects in
Developing the West
</P>
<P>
Zhang Xiaoqiang, director of the department of foreign
investment, suggested at the Asian-Pacific Economic Cooperation (
APEC) 2000 China Forum that the guiding role of the market be
fully tapped and respected, in order to avoid repetitive
construction. Moreover, enterprises should utilize their
advantages, and local governments should help facilitate the flow
of information and technology, he said, adding that blind
investment can be effectively avoided in this way.
</P>
