<HEADLINE> Death Toll Rises to 13 in Dongyuan Bus Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, May 31 (Xinhua) -- The death toll from a bus
accident Sunday afternoon in Dongyuan, Guangdong Province, has
risen to 13.
</P>
<P>
There were 37 people on the passenger bus when it veered off a
mountain highway and plunged 36 meters into a 7.5-meter-deep pond.
Rescuers have pumped water out of the pond for the salvage.
</P>
<P>
When the site was cleaned out yesterday, 13 people were
confirmed dead, instead of 12 as reported earlier. Also injured in
the accident were 24 people, including two in serious condition at
hospital.
</P>
<P>
According to the on-scene police investigation, the accident
was caused by the driver's failure to control the vehicle on the
winding road. 
</P>
