<HEADLINE> China Clamps Down On Counterfeit Money </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 31 (Xinhua) -- China's public security departments
have seized counterfeit banknotes with a combined face value of
214 million yuan during a month-long nationwide action against
fake money, the Ministry of Public Security disclosed on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The departments have so far cracked 1,800 cases of the
production and trafficking in counterfeiting money, according to
the anti-counterfeit office under the ministry.
</P>
<P>
The action was launched on April 3 when the State Council held
a special televised meeting on stopping these crimes.
</P>
<P>
The public security departments will focus their efforts on the
southeast coastal areas where counterfeiting is rampant.
</P>
<P>
According to the ministry, the action will last through
September. 
</P>
