<HEADLINE> Disaster Management Program to Be Formulated for Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, May 31 (Xinhua) -- The proposed Comprehensive Disaster
Management Program (CDMP) for Bangladesh is to be formulated by
June 2000, The Bangladesh Observer reported here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
In this regard, a Concept Paper has already been prepared
following an agreement signed recently between the Bangladeshi
government and the United Nations Development Program (UNDP) on
the need for a programmatic approach to disaster management.
</P>
<P>
The CDMP Formulation Mission is now in Bangladesh to undertake
extensive visits to disaster-prone districts, review the ongoing
disaster management efforts made by different agencies, and
conduct discussions with the stake holders, governmental and non-
governmental organizations.
</P>
<P>
The leader of the mission Nicholas Russell arrived in Dhaka on
March 15 and will stay in the country till July 7 to formulate the
Comprehensive Disaster Management Program, with the aim of
strengthening the country's existing capacity of disaster
management system to reduce risks and improve response and
recovery activities.
</P>
<P>
The Concept Paper reveals that under the CDMP "umbrella," a
number of sub-programs would be initiated. The program would be
financed by the government, interested bilateral and multilateral
donors, and implemented through appropriate governmental and non-
governmental agencies. The UNDP would support the overall
promotion, coordination and monitoring of the program.
</P>
<P>
According to the terms of reference, the CDMP Formulation
Mission will have the responsibility to develop both a Program
Support Document (PSD) for disaster management and individual
project reports on specific components within the PSD. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
