<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kuchma Urges Ways for Faster Economic Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, May 30 (Xinhua) -- Ukrainian President Leonid Kuchma
Tuesday urged the establishment of a mechanism to accelerate the
country's economic growth and achieve a growth rate of 6-7 percent
in the gross domestic product (GDP) in a couple of years.
</P>
<P>
Kuchma told a gathering of more than 300 industrialists and
entrepreneurs that Ukraine's main task in developing its economy
was to create necessary conditions for such a growth rate.
</P>
<P>
He said a mechanism for rapid economic development should be
established so that Ukraine's economy could grow in a speed 50-100
percent faster than the world level.
</P>
<P>
Kuchma said such a pace, which has been proved feasible by
domestic and foreign experts, is a decisive precondition for
economic structural reform and creative development.
</P>
<P>
If Ukraine could not achieve this objective and realistic
target, it could be eliminated in the sharp world competition and
lose everything, he said, adding Ukraine has lost a lot during the
deep and long-lasting economic crisis.
</P>
<P>
He described tax reform and investment privatization as the
effective ways to realize this target.
</P>
<P>
He called for tax reduction for corporations and individuals
and private investment, saying poorly-run companies should be
allowed to go bankrupt.
</P>
<P>
A stable exchange rate was not necessarily good to the country'
s economic development, Kuchma pointed out, saying that the
current rise in the value of hryvna, Ukraine's currency, was far
more beneficial to foreign exporters than to domestic importers.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
