<HEADLINE> S.Lankan Troops Advance On Rebel Positions In North </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, May 31 (Xinhua) -- The Sri Lankan government troops
were advancing from two locations towards Tamil rebel-held areas
in northern Jaffna Peninsula, the official Daily News reported
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Troops occupying forward defenses in Chavakachcheri, Ariyali
and Sarasalai which were partially taken control by the rebels
recently, destroyed a rebel bunker line inflicting heavy
casualties on the Tigers on Tuesday, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
Following the confrontations, the troops recovered 14 bodies of
the rebels. However, monitored Tiger transmissions revealed that a
large number of rebels were killed and wounded during the assault,
it reported.
</P>
<P>
A military spokesman was quoted as saying that the troops were
using new weapons which were having an effect on the battlefield
and which accounted for the remarkable military gains made by the
troops this week.
</P>
<P>
Last Saturday the rebels declared a unilateral ceasefire which
government rejected stating it was a ruse on the part of the
Tigers to play for time and conscript child soldiers for their
depleted ranks.
</P>
<P>
During a search carried out Tuesday following the fighting at
Ariyali and Chavakachcheri, troops recovered a large haul of arms
and ammunition left behind by the fleeing Tamil rebels.
</P>
<P>
Government troops have also destroyed two vehicles carrying
rebels when they were attempting to cross the Navatkuli bridge,
the report added..
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels, who are fighting a 17-year-old war for a
separate state for the Tamil community, are engaged in a ferocious
assault in a bid to recapture their former stronghold of Jaffna
city which they lost to the troops in the end of 1995.
</P>
</TEXT>
