<BODY>
<HEADLINE> To Quit Smoking Makes Millionaires: Specialists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, May 30 (Xinhua) -- Specialists advise smokers to quit
this habit, not only because it is harmful to human health, but it
can also make millionaires.
</P>
<P>
This is an advice put forward by doctors in the southern German
city of Munich on the eve of the World Health Organization's World
No-Tobacco Day on May 31.
</P>
<P>
They assume that if a smoker, who smokes one package every day,
quits this addiction, he will save five Germany marks per day, and
save 1825 marks a year. If he begins this "investment" when he is
only 15, with a 10 percent appreciation of cigarette prices
annually, he will become a millionaire with 2.1 million marks when
he is 65.
</P>
<P>
According to WTO statistics, an estimated four million people
die each year from tobacco-linked diseases, more than the toll
from AIDS, drug abuse, road accidents and murders. Globally,
around six trillion packs of cigarettes are sold each year,
doubling the figure in 1970, according to the WHO. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
