<HEADLINE> Scotland Beats Ireland in Soccer Friendly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, May 30 (Xinhua) -- Scotland defeated Ireland 2-1 in a
soccer friendly match in Dublin on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Everton striker Don Hutchison became the hero of the match,
scoring one goal and creating the other during the play.
</P>
<P>
Hutchison, recently transfer listed by his club after failing
to agree a new contract, capped a fine individual performance by
popping up on his own goalline to block a shot by Robbie Keane as
Ireland pressed for an equalizer in the closing seconds.
</P>
<P>
Ireland were without Manchester United captain Roy Keane and a
number of other regulars and were outplayed in midfield by a neat
passing Scotland team.
</P>
<P>
Victory for Scotland over their neighbors from across the Irish
Sea means they have now won three of seven matches played between
the two teams, Ireland having won two and the other two resulting
in draws.
</P>
<P>
Both sides failed to qualify for this summer's Euro 2000
tournament and are seeking to prepare for World Cup qualifying
campaigns beginning this autumn. 
