<HEADLINE> England Rest Owen and Wise in Soccer Friendly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, May 30 (Xinhua) -- England manager Kevin Keegan has
decided to pull Michael Owen and Dennis Wise out of Wednesday's
Wembley friendly against Ukraine because of "slight" back injuries.
</P>
<P>
Keegan confirmed Real Madrid star Steve McManaman would start
and Liverpool midfielder Steven Gerrard is also likely to make his
full debut.
</P>
<P>
The manager also revealed that Gerrard's Liverpool team-mate
Jamie Redknapp and Arsenal midfielder Ray Parlour are to have
scans on knee injuries.
</P>
<P>
"Jamie Redknapp and Ray Parlour are at this moment in time
being scanned," Keegan said.
</P>
<P>
"Everyone trained on Tuesday morning, with the exception of
Michael Owen and Dennis Wise - both have got slightly sore backs,"
he said. "It's nothing serious, just as a precaution I've pulled
them out. Certainly I won't consider those two for the game."
</P>
<P>
Keegan, who has yet to announce his team, said: "Certainly
Steven Gerrard and Steve McManaman will play. They are the only
two who know they are playing."
</P>
<P>
"Everything I've seen about Gerrard tells me he will shine at
international level. Steve McManaman will be given an absolute
free role, I think he deserves that opportunity," he added.
</P>
<P>
"I've always asked him to do something a bit different for
England. I may well ask him again in Euro 2000 to do something
different, but for the Ukraine game I'm going to say to him go on
and do what you have done for Madrid for the last six to eight
weeks. And we'll work around you. Macca has earned that right,"
said the manager. 
</P>
</TEXT>
