<HEADLINE> Cuban Sugar Output Increases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cuban sugar production dropped from 8.4 million tons in 1990 to
3.2 million tons in 1998, the lowest in history, with the arrival
of the economic crisis at the start of the last decade.
</P>
<P>
The harvest entered a process of frank recovery with 3.7
million tons last year, after several organization measures and
with the improvement of the country's economic situation.
</P>
<P>
The sugar industry continues being the main economic support of
Cuba and employs some 300,000 persons.  
</P>
