<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, May 31 (Xinhua) -- A light plane crashed and its
two occupants died in Mexico's northwestern state of Sinaloa,
local authorities said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred at 09:00 local time Tuesday near the
village of Sianuri, the destiny of the aircraft that had taken off
the airport of Culiacan, the state capital, according to the
