rally in the previous session. Frankfurt and London closed
marginally lower.
</P>
<P>
London's FTSE 100 index closed down 0.3 point at 6359.30, its
fall limited by strong performances by its two largest oil and gas
shares. BP Amoco and Shell Transport &AMP; Trading, which each added
more than 2 percent.
</P>
<P>
Computer services provider CMG led the market with a 12.5
percent advance as investors moved in to pick up a stock that has
slid sharply in recent weeks.
</P>
<P>
