percent, and rival Barclays was 1.5 percent lower at the close.
</P>
<P>
In Frankfurt, the Xetra Dax closed down 10 points, or 0.13
percent, at 7109.67, having drifted in and out of the red during
the session.
</P>
<P>
The CAC 40 in Paris was the best performer of the region,
closing up 100.77 points at 6426.26 as the market surged in late
afternoon. 
