<HEADLINE> Greece's Left-Wing Political Party Criticizes NATO Exercise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
ATHENS, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Greece's Coalition of the Left
party Wednesday criticized the ongoing NATO military exercise "
Dynamic Mix 2000," which is now taking place in Greece.
</P>
<P>
In an announcement issued Wednesday, the left-wing political
party said that the exercise was part of the "new role" of NATO's
presence in the Balkan region, inaugurated with last year's war
against Yugoslavia, which did not promote stability in the region
but, on the contrary, undermine it.
</P>
<P>
The party also accused NATO of watching ethnic cleasing being
carried out against the Serbs in the Yugoslav province of Kosovo
with indifference.
</P>
<P>
Dynamic Mix 2000, which began on May 20 and will end on June
10, involves more than 10,000 soldiers from the U.S. and another
10 NATO countries, 65 navy vessels and 293 warplanes.
</P>
<P>
It is NATO's largest exercise this year and is the first
practical application of the alliance's new structure. 
</P>
