<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Tens of thousands of
Argentines concentrated Wednesday in the Plaza de Mayo, across
from the Government House, to demonstrate against the government
adjustment policy and to reject the presence of an International
Monetary Fund (IMF) mission in the country.
</P>
<P>
The demonstration was called by the dissident General Workers
Federation (CGT), which was joined by the members of the labor
unions of state public servants, students associations, teachers,
justice workers, and small and medium businessmen.
